persName.note:
Robert Sanders (c.1727–1783), possibly the hack writer and biographer, aka Nathaniel
                            Spencer, who produced travel accounts of Scotland among other places;
                            he did not hold a medical degree.

James Hope (later Hope-Johnstone;
                            1741-1816), 3rd earl of Hopetoun on succeeding his father, John, in
                            1781; army officer.
